@startuml
' ============================================================
' Diagram   : Rapid Provisioning - Engine Sequence
' Section   : 14.11 Rapid Provisioning Architecture
' Type      : Sequence diagram
' Message   : Self-service requests flow through a sequence
'             manager and deployment engine to automatically
'             provision an OS, apply baselines, deploy
'             applications, and publish the cloud service.
' ============================================================

title 14.11 Rapid Provisioning\nEngine Sequence (18-Step Flow)

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam roundCorner 6
skinparam ArrowColor #555555
skinparam ParticipantBackgroundColor #F0F4F8
skinparam ParticipantBorderColor #4A6B8A
skinparam ActorBackgroundColor #F0F4F8
skinparam ActorBorderColor #4A6B8A
skinparam DatabaseBackgroundColor #F0F4F8
skinparam DatabaseBorderColor #4A6B8A
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF8DC
skinparam noteBorderColor #999999

actor "Cloud\nConsumer" as CC
participant "Self-Service\nPortal" as SSP
participant "Automated Service\nProvisioning Program" as ASPP
participant "Sequence\nManager" as SM
participant "Deployment Engine\n(Rapid Provisioning Engine)" as RPE
database "Deployment\nData Store" as DDS
participant "Sequence\nLogger" as SL
participant "Usage and\nAdministration Portal" as UAP

CC -> SSP : 1. request new server
SSP -> ASPP : forward request
ASPP -> SM : delegate

SM -> RPE : 2. prepare operating system
RPE -> DDS : 3. fetch templates\n(virtual or physical)
RPE -> RPE : 4. apply OS image\nor regular install
RPE --> SM : 5. OS ready
SM -> SL : 6. log step

SM -> RPE : 7. apply OS baseline
RPE -> RPE : 8. apply baseline
RPE --> SM : 9. baseline applied
SM -> SL : 10. log step

SM -> RPE : 11. install applications
RPE -> RPE : 12. deploy application packages
RPE --> SM : 13. apps installed
SM -> SL : 14. log step

SM -> RPE : 15. apply application\nconfiguration baseline
RPE -> RPE : 16. apply baseline
RPE --> SM : 17. config applied
SM -> SL : 18. log step

RPE --> ASPP : cloud service ready
ASPP -> UAP : finalize and publish
CC -> UAP : access service

note right of RPE
  Hypervisor rapidly creates and hosts virtual servers.
  Cloud storage device hosts templates, baselines, scripts.
  Resource replication generates IT resource instances.
end note

note left of DDS
  Deployment Data Store holds:
   server templates, server images,
   application packages, custom scripts,
   OS baseline, application configuration baseline.
  Other artifacts: application packager,
   custom scripts, sequence manager,
   sequence logger.
end note

@enduml
